\begin_layout Section
Data storage 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Along with an automated experimental setup should necessarily go a comprehensive
 data logging system to make it be able to real-time monitor what the setup
 is actually doing.
 Since no such logging system was present at CINF, we have build one and
 over time this has proven to be immensly usefull.
 The core of the system is a centrally manages MySQL database running on
 a dedicated server (popularly know as 'servcinf').
 All measurements performed on the microrector setup (and gradually many
 other setups) are saved directly to the database with no temperary storage
 at the local computer.
 This has many advantages, for example it is possible to real-time monitor
 the measurements through a web-browser from anywhere in the world.
 It also ensures that all data are secured even in the event of the computer
 crashes (an all to frequent event when using LabView for data aquisition....)
 and is continously backed up by the central IT-department.
 Also the central server act as a common entrance point when searching for
 old data, either ones own data or data from other CINF setups that could
 have results relevant for the current project.
 The data can be easily accessed either from the web-interface or directly
 from the database.
 Almost all figure in this thesis is thus made by very simple python-scripts
 which extracts data from the database and plots them in a consistent way.
 Besides storage of the individual measurents, the system also continously
 logs health information of the chamber, such as chamber pressure, sample
 temperature, roughing pump pressures, etc..
 in this way it is easy to catch a devoloping problem from eg.
 a rouging pump needing servce or to pin-point when a UHV chamber developed
 a leak.
\end_layout

